      <div xml:id="NA46-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu pirivuṇarttiya talaivaṟkut (ET: talaimakaṟkut; G1+2: tam) tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said to HIM who informed [her] about the separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA46">
        <lg type="edition">
            <l>vaika ṟōṟu miṉpamu miḷamaiyu</l>
            <l>meykaṇai niḻaliṟ kaḻiyumiv vulakattuk</l>
            <l>kāṇī reṉṟalō varitē yatunaṉi</l>
            <l>pēṇī rākuvi raiyaveṉ ṟōḻi</l>
            <l>pūṇaṇi yākam pulampap pāṇa</l>
            <l>rayirppukkoṇ ṭaṉṉa koṉṟaiyan tīṅkaṉi</l>
            <l rend="indent4">ruyirppiṉ ṉalyā ḻuṭaimarup paṉṉa</l>
            <l rend="indent4">vūḻuṟupu viḷainta koṉṟaiyan tīṅkaṉi</l>
            <l>paṟaiyaṟai kaṭippi ṉaṟaiyaṟaiyāt tuyalvara</l>
            <l>vevvaḷi vaḻaṅkum vēypayi laḻuvat</l>
            <l>tevva mikūu maruñcura miṟantu</l>
            <l>naṉvā yallā vāḻkkai</l> 
            <l>maṉṉāp poruṭpiṇip piritumyā meṉavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Is it difficult to say:</l>
<l rend="indent2">“you don't see [it]</l>
<l rend="indent2">in this world, where each day pleasure and youth</l>
<l rend="indent2">pass by like the shadow of an arrow discharged”?</l>
<l>You are not one to pay much heed to that, sir,</l>
<l rend="indent2">saying “we separate”, enticed by impermanent wealth,</l>
<l rend="indent2">a living without good truth(?)<note place="foot">What is the significance of <term xml:lang="ta">nal-vāy</term> here?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">traversing the difficult desert where distress abounds,</l>
<l rend="indent">in the rustling bamboo depth, where hot winds are wandering</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that the sweet ripe Laburnum fruits come into swaying,</l>
<l rend="indent2">hitting the rock like a drumstick beating a drum</l>
<l rend="indent3">as if the bard had been seized by doubt<note place="foot">The point of the image seems to be that the sound is irregular: sometimes the wind drives the fruit towards the rock, and then it suddenly stops again. In any case the context shows that the ambiguous viṉaiyeccam form <term xml:lang="ta">aṟaiyā</term> has to be taken in a positive sense.</note>,</l>
<l>while my friend, [her] breast decked with ornaments,</l>
<l rend="indent2">will be lonely.</l>
        </lg>
